The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Nov. 10: Mixed signals have emerged on ONGC Videsh Limiteds (OVL) proposed acquisition of UKs Imperial Energy. Sources said a section in the petroleum ministry was in favour of OVL renegotiating the deal as the valuation had been made by the firm when crude and stock prices were both substantially high although OVL was keen on going ahead with the deal.                            
	 London, Nov. 10: HSBCs pre-tax profits had risen in the third-quarter despite loan write-offs in the United States rising to $4.3 billion. The global banking giant said that loan impairment charges in the United States rose by $700 million from the second quarter.                             
	 Washington, Nov. 10: The US government has restructured its bailout of American International Group Inc (AIG), raising the package to a record $150 billion with easier terms, after a smaller rescue plan failed to stabilise the ailing insurance giant.                            
	 New Delhi, Nov. 10: The department of telecom is likely to finalise tomorrow the additional fee to be charged from existing GSM players who have acquired spectrum beyond the contracted limit of 6.2 MHz.                            
	 Kuala Lumpur, Nov. 10: Satyam Computer Services will absorb 128 employees of Motorolas Software Development Centre, acquired by the IT services provider.                                                                                                                         
